sql:
SELECT plant_id, plant_name
FROM power_plants
WHERE location = 'location1';

SELECT location, COUNT(*) AS plant_count
FROM power_plants
GROUP BY location;

SELECT machines.machine_name, power_plants.plant_name 
FROM machines
JOIN power_plants ON machines.plant_id = power_plants.plant_id;

SELECT plant_name
FROM power_plants
WHERE environmental_rating = (
  SELECT MAX(environmental_rating)
  FROM power_plants
);

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed beyond their infancy" refers to machines that have been operational for more than 10 days;
- "standing tall in the operational field" refers to machines that are either active or enabled and are part of operational power plants;
- "flourishing with efficiency metrics" refers to the performance metrics for efficiency where values are greater than 0.60;
- "measure of their blooming efficiency" refers to the average of these efficiency metrics over the period.

sql:
SELECT plant_name
FROM power_plants
WHERE capacity > 100 AND commission_date < '2010-01-01';

SELECT AVG(sensor_count) AS average_sensor_count
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(sensor_id) AS sensor_count
  FROM sensors
  GROUP BY plant_id
);

SELECT AVG(capacity) AS avg_capacity
FROM power_plants
WHERE location = 'New York';

external_knowledge:
- "bustling with activity" refers to the plant being in an 'active' status;
- "large capacity over 1000 MW" refers to plants with a capacity greater than 1000.0 MW;
- "runs on natural gas" indicates the fuel type is 'natural gas';
- "somewhat eco-friendly" corresponds to the environmental rating of 'B'.
- "facility that's bustling with activity" also applies to the conditions for the sensor and machine being active;
- "temperature sensor" and "turbine" refer to the specific types of sensors and machines.
